  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get two large frying pans over a high heat and drizzle a little oil\ninto each. Place the chipolatas in one of the pans. Space out the\nrashers of bacon in the other."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop the mushrooms, then chuck them into the pan with\nthe bacon. Nestle the cherry tomatoes between the sausages in\nthe pan. Fry for about 8 mins, turning the sausages and bacon\nwhen needed, until everything is cooked through and to your\nliking. Turn down the heat on the bacon pan if it is crisp before\nthe sausages are done."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, crack the eggs into a large measuring jug. Whisk\ntogether with a fork and season well with salt and black pepper.\nAdd a knob of butter. Blast in the microwave for 30 seconds at a time, stirring after each blast, until you have super creamy\nscrambled eggs. Stop cooking just before the eggs are set as\nthey will carry on cooking in the jug."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Toast the bread and put it onto a plate. Serve the sausages,\ntomatoes, bacon, mushrooms, scrambled eggs and toast at the\ntable, with plenty of condiments for people to help themselves."
    }
  ],
